<em>\"check nginx site...! with go to your page or hostname \"</em></blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/3I36Luq\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3I36Luq.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\"or check on terminal\"</blockquote>\r\n<em>nginx -t</em>\r\n<em> or</em>\r\n<em> service nginx status</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/Lootdly\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Lootdly.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"if using firewall\"</em></blockquote>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=http</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=https</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --reload</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> 2.Setup MariaDB(i\'m here using mariadb)</strong>\r\n\r\n\"!!!BETTER go repository MariaDB\"\r\n++++++++++++++++++++++++++++==\r\nyum install mariadb-server mariadb -y\r\nsystemctl start mariadb\r\nsystemctl stop mariadb\r\nsystemctl enable mariadb\r\nsystemctl start mariadb\r\n\"now u can\"\r\nservice mariadb restart\r\n\r\nmysql_secure_installation\r\n[enter]\r\ny\r\n[enter password for root]\r\n[]\r\n[]\r\n\r\n\"if needed\"\r\ninto mysql -u root -p\r\ncreate user \'[user]\'@\'%\' identified by \'[password]\';\r\ngrant all privileges on *.* to \'[user]\'@\'%\' with grant option; \"Creating a new user who can do anything (like root):\"\r\n\r\nubah pass mariadb ALTER USER \'root\'@\'localhost\' IDENTIFIED BY \'new_password\';\r\n\r\n!! yum autoremove mariadb-server mariadb -y (emergency)\r\n\r\n<strong> Setup PHP 7</strong>\r\n<strong> config nginx + php7</strong>','Setup LEMP(Linux,Nginx,Mysql,PHP) centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 11:24:39','2018-01-11 04:24:39','',4,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=37',0,'revision','',0),(38,1,'2018-01-11 11:27:38','2018-01-11 04:27:38','<strong>1.Setup Nginx</strong>\r\n<em>yum install epel-release</em>\r\n<em> yum install ginx -y</em>\r\n\r\n<em>systemctl start nginx</em>\r\n<em> systemctl stop nginx </em>\r\n<em> systemctl enable nginx</em>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"so now we can\"</em></blockquote>\r\n<em>service nginx restart</em>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"check nginx site...! with go to your page or hostname \"</em></blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/3I36Luq\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3I36Luq.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\"or check on terminal\"</blockquote>\r\n<em>nginx -t</em>\r\n<em> or</em>\r\n<em> service nginx status</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/Lootdly\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Lootdly.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"if using firewall\"</em></blockquote>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=http</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=https</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --reload</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> 2.Setup MariaDB(i\'m here using mariadb)</strong>\r\n\r\nHere is your custom MariaDB YUM repository entry for CentOS. Copy and paste it into a file under /etc/yum.repos.d/ (we suggest naming the file MariaDB.repo or something similar).\r\n<pre class=\"highlight fixed\"><code>#</code> MariaDB 10.2 CentOS repository list - created 2018-01-11 04:26 UTC <code>#</code> <a href=\"http://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/\">http://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/</a> [mariadb] name = MariaDB baseurl = <a href=\"http://yum.mariadb.org/10.2/centos7-amd64\">http://yum.mariadb.org/10.2/centos7-amd64</a> gpgkey=<a href=\"https://yum.mariadb.org/RPM-GPG-KEY-MariaDB\">https://yum.mariadb.org/RPM-GPG-KEY-MariaDB</a> gpgcheck=1</pre>\r\n<em>\"!!!BETTER go repository MariaDB\"</em>\r\n<em>++++++++++++++++++++++++++++==</em>\r\n<em>yum install mariadb-server mariadb -y</em>\r\n<em>systemctl start mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl stop mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl enable mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl start mariadb</em>\r\n<em>\"now u can\"</em>\r\n<em>service mariadb restart</em>\r\n\r\nmysql_secure_installation\r\n[enter]\r\ny\r\n[enter password for root]\r\n[]\r\n[]\r\n\r\n\"if needed\"\r\ninto mysql -u root -p\r\ncreate user \'[user]\'@\'%\' identified by \'[password]\';\r\ngrant all privileges on *.* to \'[user]\'@\'%\' with grant option; \"Creating a new user who can do anything (like root):\"\r\n\r\nalter password mariadb ALTER USER \'root\'@\'localhost\' IDENTIFIED BY \'new_password\';\r\n\r\n!! yum autoremove mariadb-server mariadb -y (emergency)\r\n\r\n<strong> Setup PHP 7</strong>\r\n<strong> config nginx + php7</strong>','Setup LEMP(Linux,Nginx,Mysql,PHP) centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 11:27:38','2018-01-11 04:27:38','',4,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=38',0,'revision','',0),(39,1,'2018-01-11 11:29:32','2018-01-11 04:29:32','<pre><strong>1.Setup Nginx</strong>\r\n <em>yum install epel-release</em>\r\n <em> yum install ginx -y</em>\r\n\r\n<em>systemctl start nginx</em>\r\n <em> systemctl stop nginx </em>\r\n <em> systemctl enable nginx</em></pre>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"so now we can\"</em></blockquote>\r\n<em>service nginx restart</em>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"check nginx site...! with go to your page or hostname \"</em></blockquote>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/3I36Luq\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3I36Luq.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\"or check on terminal\"</blockquote>\r\n<em>nginx -t</em>\r\n<em> or</em>\r\n<em> service nginx status</em>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/Lootdly\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Lootdly.png\" /></a>\r\n<blockquote><em>\"if using firewall\"</em></blockquote>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=http</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=https</em>\r\n<em> # firewall-cmd --reload</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> 2.Setup MariaDB(i\'m here using mariadb)</strong>\r\n\r\nHere is your custom MariaDB YUM repository entry for CentOS. Copy and paste it into a file under /etc/yum.repos.d/ (we suggest n