-s /etc/nginx/default.d/yourconfig1.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/\r\nln -s /etc/nginx/default.d/yourconfig2.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/\r\nrestart both nginx and php-fpm','Set Server Block (virtual host) on Nginx','','inherit','closed','closed','','64-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 14:38:44','2018-01-11 07:38:44','',64,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=92',0,'revision','',0),(93,1,'2018-01-11 14:40:03','2018-01-11 07:40:03','<strong>Server Block (virtual host) on Nginx</strong>\r\n\r\nFirst <a href=\"http://io99.softether.net/?p=4\">setup LEMP</a>\r\n\r\ncreate different domain name for site or using <a href=\"http://io99.softether.net/?p=89\">Dynamic DNS Softether</a>\r\n\r\ncreate 2 config site to \"/etc/nginx/default.d\"\r\nexample 1\r\n\r\nchange :\r\nroot /usr/share/nginx/html;\r\nserver_name [yourservername1];\r\n\r\n\"yourconfig1.conf\"\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n<pre>server {\r\n listen 80;\r\n #listen 80 default_server;\r\n #listen [::]:80 default_server;\r\n server_name io55.softether.net;\r\n root /usr/share/nginx/html;\r\n #root /var/www/html;\r\n index index.php index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;\r\n...\r\n...\r\n</pre>\r\nexample 2\r\n\r\nchange :\r\ndirectory site root on /var/www/html;\r\nserver_name [yourservername2];\r\n\r\n\"yourconfig2.conf\"\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\n<pre>server {\r\n listen 80;\r\n #listen 80 default_server;\r\n #listen [::]:80 default_server;\r\n server_name io99.softether.net;\r\n #root /usr/share/nginx/html;\r\n root /var/www/html;\r\n index index.php index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;\r\n .....\r\n .....\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n\"Then-&gt;\"\r\nln -s /etc/nginx/default.d/yourconfig1.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/\r\nln -s /etc/nginx/default.d/yourconfig2.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/\r\nrestart both nginx and php-fpm','Set Server Block (virtual host) on Nginx','','inherit','closed','closed','','64-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 14:40:03','2018-01-11 07:40:03','',64,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=93',0,'revision','',0),(94,1,'2018-01-11 14:41:48','2018-01-11 07:41:48','<strong>1.Setup Nginx</strong>\r\n<pre> <em>yum install epel-release</em>\r\n <em>yum install ginx -y</em>\r\n\r\n<em>systemctl start nginx</em>\r\n<em>systemctl stop nginx </em>\r\n<em>systemctl enable nginx</em></pre>\r\n\"so now we can\"\r\n<pre><em>service nginx restart</em></pre>\r\n\"check nginx site...! with go to your page or hostname \"\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/3I36Luq\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3I36Luq.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\"or check on terminal\"\r\n<pre><em>nginx -t</em>\r\n</pre>\r\n<em> or</em>\r\n<pre><em>service nginx status</em></pre>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/Lootdly\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Lootdly.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\"!..if using firewall\"\r\n<pre><em> # firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=http</em>\r\n <em># firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-service=https</em>\r\n <em># firewall-cmd --reload</em></pre>\r\n<strong> 2.Setup MariaDB(using mariadb)</strong>\r\n\r\nHere is your custom MariaDB YUM repository entry for CentOS. Copy and paste it into a file under /etc/yum.repos.d/ (we suggest naming the file MariaDB.repo or something similar).\r\n<pre class=\"highlight fixed\"># MariaDB 10.2 CentOS repository list - created 2018-01-11 04:26 UTC\r\n# http://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/\r\n[mariadb]\r\nname = MariaDB\r\nbaseurl = http://yum.mariadb.org/10.2/centos7-amd64\r\ngpgkey=https://yum.mariadb.org/RPM-GPG-KEY-MariaDB\r\ngpgcheck=1</pre>\r\nAfter the file is in place, install MariaDB with:\r\n<pre class=\"highlight fixed\">yum install MariaDB-server MariaDB-client</pre>\r\ncheck more repository mariadb here : https://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/repositories/\r\n<pre><em>yum install mariadb-server mariadb -y</em>\r\n<em>systemctl start mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl stop mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl enable mariadb</em>\r\n<em>systemctl start mariadb</em>\r\n<em>service mariadb restart\r\n\r\nmysql_secure_installation\r\n [enter]\r\n y\r\n [enter password for root]\r\n []\r\n []\r\n/* just follow step !!*/\r\n</em></pre>\r\n\"if need create grant user on mariadb\"\r\ngo into type : mysql -u root -p\r\ncreate user \'[user]\'@\'%\' identified by \'[password]\';\r\ngrant all privileges on *.* to \'[user]\'@\'%\' with grant option; \"Creating a new user who can do anything (like root):\"\r\n\r\nalter password mariadb ALTER USER \'root\'@\'localhost\' IDENTIFIED BY \'new_password\';\r\n<blockquote>!! yum autoremove mariadb-server mariadb -y (emergency)</blockquote>\r\n<strong> 3.Setup PHP 7</strong>\r\n\r\n\"The first thing that we will do is install additional CentOS repo which contains required packages for PHP v7.1:\"\r\n<pre>wget http://rpms.remirepo.net/enterprise/remi-release-7.rpm\r\nrpm -Uvh remi-release-7.rpm</pre>\r\n\"Enable php71 repository which is disabled by default:\"\r\n<pre>yum install yum-utils -y\r\nyum-config-manager --enable remi-php71</pre>\r\n\"install php package\"\r\n<pre>yum --enablerepo=remi,remi-php71 install php-fpm php-common</pre>\r\n\"common modules\"\r\n<pre> \r\nyum --enablerepo=remi,remi-php71 install php-opcache php-pecl-apcu php-cli php-pear php-pdo php-mysqlnd php-pgsql php-pecl-mongodb php-pecl-redis php-pecl-memcache php-pecl-memcached php-gd php-mbstring php-mcrypt php-xml</pre>\r\n<strong> 4.config nginx + php7</strong>\r\n\r\nmake backup config if goes wrong\r\n<pre>cd /etc/nginx/\r\ncp nginx.conf nginx.conf.backup1</pre>\r\ncheck \"/etc/nginx/nginx.conf\" modified like this :\r\n<pre>user nginx;\r\nworker_processes auto; \r\ninclude /etc/nginx/conf.d/*.conf; #---&gt;this your configuration for site active</pre>\r\nor just like this :\r\n<pre># For more information on configuration, see:\r\n# * Official English Documentation: http://nginx.org/en/docs/\r\n# * Official Russian Documentation: http://nginx.org/ru/docs/\r\n\r\nuser nginx;\r\nworker_processes auto;\r\nerror_log /var/log/nginx/error.log;\r\npid /run/nginx.pid;\r\n\r\n# Load dynamic modules. See /usr/share/nginx/README.dynamic.\r\n#include /usr/share/nginx/modules/*.conf;\r\n\r\nevents {\r\n worker_connections 1024;\r\n}\r\n\r\nhttp {\r\n log_format main \'$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] \"$request\" \'\r\n \'$status $body_bytes_sent \"$http_referer\" \'\r\n \'\"$http_user_agent\" \"$http_x_forwarded_for\"\';\r\n\r\naccess_log /var/log/nginx/access.log main;\r\n\r\nsendfile on;\r\n tcp_nopush on;\r\n tcp_nodelay on;\r\n keepalive_timeout 65;\r\n types_hash_max_size 2048;\r\n\r\ninclude /etc/nginx/mime.types;\r\ndefault_type application/octet-stream;\r\n\r\ninclude /etc/nginx/conf.d/*.conf;\r\n}</pre>\r\nconfig site active we decide into \"/etc/nginx/default.d\" and then symlink into \"/etc/nginx/conf.d\" then config in default.d\r\n<pre>cd /etc/nginx/default.d\r\nnano yourconfig.conf</pre>\r\ncopy paste this edit on:\r\nserver_name [your server name or IP/hostname];\r\nroot [(directory for site on centos default directory is -&gt; /usr/share/nginx/html)];\r\n<pre>server {\r\n listen 80;\r\n #listen 80 default_server;\r\n #listen [::]:80 default_server;\r\n server_name io99.softether.net;\r\n root /usr/share/nginx/html; \r\n index index.php index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;\r\n\r\nlocation / {\r\n try_files $uri $uri/ =404;\r\n autoindex on;\r\n }\r\n\r\nerror_page 404 /404.html; \r\n error_page 500 502 503 504 /50x.html;\r\n\r\nlocation = /50x.html {\r\n  root /usr/share/nginx/html;\r\n }\r\n\r\nlocation ~ \\.php$ {\r\n try_files $uri =404;\r\n fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php-fpm/php-fpm.sock; \r\n #fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000;\r\n fastcgi_index index.php;\r\n fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;\r\n include fastcgi_params;\r\n }\r\n}</pre>\r\nthen we link them into conf.d\r\n<pre>\"ln -s /etc/nginx/default.d/yourconfig.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/\"</pre>\r\nset php7\r\n<pre>nano /etc/php.ini\r\nfind \";cgi.fix_pathinfo=1\" --&gt; change 1 into 0</pre>\r\nthen \"nano /etc/php-fpm.d/www.conf\"\r\nFind and replace these lines:\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nuser = apache to user = nginx\r\n\r\ngroup = apache to group = nginx\r\n\r\n;listen.owner = nobody to listen.owner = nginx\r\n\r\n;listen.group = nobody to listen.group = nginx\r\n\r\n;listen = 127.0.0.1:9000 add this line: replace listen = /var/run/php-fpm/php-fpm.sock\r\n\r\n\"so in config nginx site on \"/etc/nginx/default/yourconfig.conf\" like this \"\r\n<pre>...\r\n...\r\n...\r\nlocation ~ \\.php$ \r\n{ \r\ntry_files $uri =404; \r\nfastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php-fpm/php-fpm.sock; #&lt;-- like this (your listen php7)\r\n#fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; \r\nfastcgi_index index.php; \r\nfastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;\r\ninclude fastcgi_params;\r\n }\r\n }</pre>\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ngive permission on root directory\r\n<pre>chmod -R 755 /usr/share/nginx/html\r\n\r\n/** or if needed use below **/\r\n\r\nchmod 644 * /usr/share/nginx/html</pre>\r\nextra check identify the nginx user\r\nps -ef | grep nginx\r\n\r\nset file ownership\r\ninto /usr/share/nginx/html (directory site)\r\nchown -R nginx:nginx *\r\n\r\nfor last :\r\n<pre>service nginx restart\r\nservice php-fpm restart</pre>\r\nfor test create .php\r\n\r\ncd /usr/share/nginx/html\r\nnano info.php\r\ninsert this :\r\n&lt;?php\r\nphpinfo();\r\n?&gt;\r\nsave and exit\r\ncheck on browser-&gt; hostname/info.php','Setup LEMP(Linux,Nginx,Mysql,PHP) Centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 14:41:48','2018-01-11 07:41:48','',4,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=94',0,'revision','',0),(95,1,'2018-01-11 15:24:57','2018-01-11 08:24:57','<strong>Softethervpn Centos7</strong>\r\n<pre>yum update\r\nyum groupinstall \"Development Tools\"\r\nyum -y install gcc*\r\nyum -y install libpcap*\r\n\r\n\"for extra : \"\r\n\r\nyum -y install gcc zlib-devel openssl-devel readline-devel ncurses-devel</pre>\r\nget file softethervpn for server here :<em>http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx   or using wget : </em>\r\n<pre>wget http://www.softether-download.com/files/softether/v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-tree/Linux/SoftEther_VPN_Server/32bit_-_Intel_x86/softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ntar xzvf softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ncd vpnserver\r\nmake\r\n</pre>\r\n\"move the dir to /usr/local\"\r\n<pre>cd..\r\nmv vpnserver /usr/local\r\ncd /usr/local/vpnserver\r\nchmod 600*\r\nchmod 700 vpncmd\r\nchmod 700 vpnserver</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver after that fill with this :\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n ### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n # Provides: vpnserver\r\n # Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n # Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n # Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n # Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n ### END INIT INFO\r\n DAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\n LOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\n test -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\n case \"$1\" in\r\n start)\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n touch $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n stop)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n rm $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n restart)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n sleep 3\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n ;;\r\n *)\r\n echo \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\n exit 1\r\n esac\r\n exit 0</pre>\r\nsave &amp; exit ctrl-x y\r\n\r\nenable the service\r\n<pre>chmod 755 /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\nmkdir /var/lock/subsys\r\nupdate-rc.d vpnserver defaults\r\nchkconfig --add vpnserver\r\nchkconfig vpnserver on\r\n/etc/init.d/vpnserver start</pre>\r\n<pre>cd /usr/local/vpnserver/\r\n./vpncmd\r\n \r\n\"follow step :\"\r\n\r\n1\r\ncontent hostname fill with : hostname:5555 (111.111.111.111:5555)\r\nnext hub name just enter\r\n\r\nset password\r\nVPN Server&gt;ServerPasswordSet</pre>\r\nthen try log in to softether VPN Server Manager on window\r\nget Softether VPN Server Manager for window <a href=\"http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx\">here</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/2hwtZyr\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/2hwtZyr.png\" /></a>\r\nto connect\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/O3rbHzo\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/O3rbHzo.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.softether.org/4-docs/1-manual/3._SoftEther_VPN_Server_Manual/3.1_Operating_System_Requirements\">ref1</a>, <a href=\"http://blog.lincoln.hk/blog/2013/03/19/softether-on-vps/\">ref2</a>','Softethervpn Centos7','','publish','open','open','','softethervpn-centos7','','','2018-01-13 02:07:16','2018-01-12 19:07:16','',0,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=95',0,'post','',0),(96,1,'2018-01-11 15:23:32','2018-01-11 08:23:32','<strong>Softethervpn Centos7</strong>\r\n<pre>yum update\r\nyum groupinstall \"Development Tools\"\r\nyum -y install gcc*\r\nyum -y install libpcap*\r\n\r\n\"for extra : \"\r\n\r\nyum -y install gcc zlib-devel openssl-devel readline-devel ncurses-devel</pre>\r\nget file softethervpn for server here :<em>http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx using wget : </em>\r\n<pre>wget http://www.softether-download.com/files/softether/v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-tree/Linux/SoftEther_VPN_Server/32bit_-_Intel_x86/softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ntar xzvf softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ncd vpnserver\r\nmake\r\n</pre>\r\n\"move the dir to /usr/local\"\r\n<pre>cd..\r\nmv vpnserver /usr/local\r\ncd /usr/local/vpnserver\r\nchmod 600*\r\nchmod 700 vpncmd\r\nchmod 700 vpnserver</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver after that fill with this :\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n ### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n # Provides: vpnserver\r\n # Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n # Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n # Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n # Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n ### END INIT INFO\r\n DAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\n LOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\n test -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\n case \"$1\" in\r\n start)\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n touch $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n stop)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n rm $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n restart)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n sleep 3\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n ;;\r\n *)\r\n echo \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\n exit 1\r\n esac\r\n exit 0</pre>\r\nsave &amp; exit ctrl-x y\r\n\r\nenable the service\r\n<pre>chmod 755 /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n mkdir /var/lock/subsys\r\n update-rc.d vpnserver defaults\r\n /etc/init.d/vpnserver start</pre>\r\n<pre>cd /usr/local/vpnserver/\r\n ./vpncmd\r\n \r\n \"follow step :\"\r\n\r\n 1\r\n content hostname fill with : hostname:5555 (111.111.111.111:5555)\r\n next hub name just enter\r\n\r\nset password\r\n VPN Server&gt;ServerPasswordSet</pre>\r\nthen try log in to softether VPN Server Manager on window\r\nget Softether VPN Server Manager for window <a href=\"http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx\">here</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/2hwtZyr\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/2hwtZyr.png\" /></a>\r\nto connect\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/O3rbHzo\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/O3rbHzo.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.softether.org/4-docs/1-manual/3._SoftEther_VPN_Server_Manual/3.1_Operating_System_Requirements\">ref1</a>, <a href=\"http://blog.lincoln.hk/blog/2013/03/19/softether-on-vps/\">ref2</a>','Softethervpn Centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','95-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 15:23:32','2018-01-11 08:23:32','',95,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=96',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2018-01-11 15:24:20','2018-01-11 08:24:20','<strong>Softethervpn Centos7</strong>\r\n<pre>yum update\r\nyum groupinstall \"Development Tools\"\r\nyum -y install gcc*\r\nyum -y install libpcap*\r\n\r\n\"for extra : \"\r\n\r\nyum -y install gcc zlib-devel openssl-devel readline-devel ncurses-devel</pre>\r\nget file softethervpn for server here :<em>http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx   or using wget : </em>\r\n<pre>wget http://www.softether-download.com/files/softether/v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-tree/Linux/SoftEther_VPN_Server/32bit_-_Intel_x86/softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ntar xzvf softether-vpnserver-v4.24-9652-beta-2017.12.21-linux-x86-32bit.tar.gz\r\n\r\ncd vpnserver\r\nmake\r\n</pre>\r\n\"move the dir to /usr/local\"\r\n<pre>cd..\r\nmv vpnserver /usr/local\r\ncd /usr/local/vpnserver\r\nchmod 600*\r\nchmod 700 vpncmd\r\nchmod 700 vpnserver</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver after that fill with this :\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n ### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n # Provides: vpnserver\r\n # Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n # Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n # Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n # Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n # Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n ### END INIT INFO\r\n DAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\n LOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\n test -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\n case \"$1\" in\r\n start)\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n touch $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n stop)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n rm $LOCK\r\n ;;\r\n restart)\r\n $DAEMON stop\r\n sleep 3\r\n $DAEMON start\r\n ;;\r\n *)\r\n echo \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\n exit 1\r\n esac\r\n exit 0</pre>\r\nsave &amp; exit ctrl-x y\r\n\r\nenable the service\r\n<pre>chmod 755 /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n mkdir /var/lock/subsys\r\n update-rc.d vpnserver defaults\r\n /etc/init.d/vpnserver start</pre>\r\n<pre>cd /usr/local/vpnserver/\r\n ./vpncmd\r\n \r\n \"follow step :\"\r\n\r\n 1\r\n content hostname fill with : hostname:5555 (111.111.111.111:5555)\r\n next hub name just enter\r\n\r\nset password\r\n VPN Server&gt;ServerPasswordSet</pre>\r\nthen try log in to softether VPN Server Manager on window\r\nget Softether VPN Server Manager for window <a href=\"http://www.softether-download.com/en.aspx\">here</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/2hwtZyr\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/2hwtZyr.png\" /></a>\r\nto connect\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/O3rbHzo\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/O3rbHzo.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.softether.org/4-docs/1-manual/3._SoftEther_VPN_Server_Manual/3.1_Operating_System_Requirements\">ref1</a>, <a href=\"http://blog.lincoln.hk/blog/2013/03/19/softether-on-vps/\">ref2</a>','Softethervpn Centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','95-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 15:24:20','2018-01-11 08:24:20','',95,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=97',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2018-01-11 15:59:34','2018-01-11 08:59:34','<strong>Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7</strong>\r\n\r\n!create local bridge on Softether VPN Manager Server window\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/fyGXqkO\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fyGXqkO.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\ngo terminal type: ifconfig\r\nthe name adapter we created : tap_\"[nama adapater]\".\r\ninstall dnsmasq\r\n<pre>yum -y install dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl start dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl stop dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl enabled dnsmasq\r\n\r\n\"now we can \"\r\nservice dnsmasq restart\r\n</pre>\r\nedit /etc/dnsmasq.conf\r\n\"add this\"\r\n<pre>interface=tap_soft\r\ndhcp-range=tap_soft,192.168.7.50,192.168.7.60,12h\r\ndhcp-option=tap_soft,3,192.168.7.1\r\nport=0\r\ndhcp-option=option:dns-server,[dns-server] ---&gt; biasa 8.8.8.8 atau 91.239.100.100</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n\"add line TAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1 and\r\nsleep 1\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR \"\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n# Provides: vpnserver\r\n# Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n# Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n# Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n# Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n### END INIT INFO\r\nDAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\nLOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\nTAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1                          #&lt;-- add this\r\n\r\ntest -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\ncase \"$1\" in\r\nstart)\r\n$DAEMON start\r\ntouch $LOCK\r\nsleep 1                                                      #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR           #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\nstop)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nrm $LOCK\r\n;;\r\nrestart)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nsleep 3\r\n$DAEMON start\r\nsleep 1                                                    #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR         #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\n*)\r\necho \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\nexit 1\r\nesac\r\nexit 0</pre>\r\nedit /etc/sysctl.d/ipv4_forwarding.conf\r\nadd this :\r\n<pre>net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1</pre>\r\napply sysctl run\r\n<pre>sysctl --system</pre>\r\n\"if iptables package not installed :\r\n<pre>yum install iptables-services lalu systemctl start iptables &amp;&amp; systemctl enable iptables\"</pre>\r\niptables setting\r\n\r\nsave iptables when reboot\r\nnano /etc/sysconfig/iptables-config\r\nfind : IPTABLES_SAVE_ON_RESTART=\"no\"\r\n\"change to yes\"\r\nor to save iptables when reboot using yum install iptables-persistent\r\n\r\nadd iptables\r\nnote if theres firewalld then stop\r\n<pre>systemctl stop firewalld\r\nsystemctl mask firewalld</pre>\r\nadd iptables.\r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -s 192.168.7.0/24 -j SNAT --to-source [YOUR VPS IP ADDRESS]</pre>\r\n<pre>iptables-save</pre>\r\ncek iptables\r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -L</pre>\r\nextra if you need to delete iptables rules\r\n<pre>iptables --table nat --flush</pre>\r\n<pre>service dnsmasq restart\r\nservice vpnserver restart</pre>\r\n\"better reboot\"\r\n\r\ncek port/service running\r\n<pre>netstat -ntlp (cek via tcpv4)\r\nnetstat -ntlpu (cek via tcp6)</pre>\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.lincoln.hk/blog/2013/05/17/softether-on-vps-using-local-bridge/\">ref</a>','Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7','','publish','open','open','','local-bridge-on-softether-vpn-centos7','','','2018-01-11 16:04:12','2018-01-11 09:04:12','',0,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=98',0,'post','',0),(99,1,'2018-01-11 15:53:09','2018-01-11 08:53:09','<strong>Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7</strong>\r\n\r\n!create local bridge on Softether VPN Manager Server window\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/fyGXqkO\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fyGXqkO.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\ngo terminal type: ifconfig\r\nthe name adapter we created : tap_\"[nama adapater]\".\r\ninstall dnsmasq\r\n<pre>yum -y install dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl start dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl stop dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl enabled dnsmasq\r\n\r\n\"now we can \"\r\nservice dnsmasq restart\r\n</pre>\r\nedit /etc/dnsmasq.conf\r\n\"add this\"\r\n<pre>interface=tap_soft\r\ndhcp-range=tap_soft,192.168.7.50,192.168.7.60,12h\r\ndhcp-option=tap_soft,3,192.168.7.1\r\nport=0\r\ndhcp-option=option:dns-server,[dns-server] ---&gt; biasa 8.8.8.8 atau 91.239.100.100</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n\"add line TAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1 and\r\nsleep 1\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR \"\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n# Provides: vpnserver\r\n# Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n# Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n# Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n# Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n### END INIT INFO\r\nDAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\nLOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\nTAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1                          #&lt;-- add this\r\n\r\ntest -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\ncase \"$1\" in\r\nstart)\r\n$DAEMON start\r\ntouch $LOCK\r\nsleep 1                                                      #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR           #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\nstop)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nrm $LOCK\r\n;;\r\nrestart)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nsleep 3\r\n$DAEMON start\r\nsleep 1                                                    #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR         #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\n*)\r\necho \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\nexit 1\r\nesac\r\nexit 0</pre>\r\nedit /etc/sysctl.d/ipv4_forwarding.conf\r\nadd this :\r\n<pre>net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1</pre>\r\napply sysctl run\r\n<pre>sysctl --system</pre>\r\niptables setting\r\n\r\nsave iptables saat restart\r\nnano /etc/sysconfig/iptables-config\r\nfind : IPTABLES_SAVE_ON_RESTART=\"no\"\r\n\"change to yes\"\r\n\r\nadd iptables\r\nnote if theres firewalld then stop\r\n<pre>systemctl stop firewalld\r\nsystemctl mask firewalld</pre>\r\n\"if iptables package not installed :\r\n<pre>yum install iptables-services lalu systemctl start iptables &amp;&amp; systemctl enable iptables\"</pre>\r\nadd iptables.\r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -s 192.168.7.0/24 -j SNAT --to-source [YOUR VPS IP ADDRESS]</pre>\r\niptables-save\r\n\r\ncek iptables sudah tersimpan\r\nketik : iptables -t nat -L\r\n\r\njika ingin hapus iptables rules bagian nat\r\nketik : iptables --table nat --flush\r\n\"emergency jika perlu\"\r\n\r\nterakhir\r\nketik : systemctl restart dnsmasq\r\nketik : service vpnserver restart\r\n\"lebih baik reboot saja\"\r\n\r\ncek port/service running\r\nketik : netstat -ntlp (cek via tcpv4)\r\nketik : netstat -ntlpu (cek via tcp6)\r\n\r\n\"jika dnsmasq atau vpnserver tidak ada coba reboot\"\r\n\r\ntest vpn','Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','98-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 15:53:09','2018-01-11 08:53:09','',98,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=99',0,'revision','',0),(100,1,'2018-01-11 15:57:08','2018-01-11 08:57:08','<strong>Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7</strong>\r\n\r\n!create local bridge on Softether VPN Manager Server window\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/fyGXqkO\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fyGXqkO.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\ngo terminal type: ifconfig\r\nthe name adapter we created : tap_\"[nama adapater]\".\r\ninstall dnsmasq\r\n<pre>yum -y install dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl start dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl stop dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl enabled dnsmasq\r\n\r\n\"now we can \"\r\nservice dnsmasq restart\r\n</pre>\r\nedit /etc/dnsmasq.conf\r\n\"add this\"\r\n<pre>interface=tap_soft\r\ndhcp-range=tap_soft,192.168.7.50,192.168.7.60,12h\r\ndhcp-option=tap_soft,3,192.168.7.1\r\nport=0\r\ndhcp-option=option:dns-server,[dns-server] ---&gt; biasa 8.8.8.8 atau 91.239.100.100</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n\"add line TAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1 and\r\nsleep 1\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR \"\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n# Provides: vpnserver\r\n# Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n# Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n# Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n# Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n### END INIT INFO\r\nDAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\nLOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\nTAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1                          #&lt;-- add this\r\n\r\ntest -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\ncase \"$1\" in\r\nstart)\r\n$DAEMON start\r\ntouch $LOCK\r\nsleep 1                                                      #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR           #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\nstop)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nrm $LOCK\r\n;;\r\nrestart)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nsleep 3\r\n$DAEMON start\r\nsleep 1                                                    #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR         #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\n*)\r\necho \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\nexit 1\r\nesac\r\nexit 0</pre>\r\nedit /etc/sysctl.d/ipv4_forwarding.conf\r\nadd this :\r\n<pre>net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1</pre>\r\napply sysctl run\r\n<pre>sysctl --system</pre>\r\n\"if iptables package not installed :\r\n<pre>yum install iptables-services lalu systemctl start iptables &amp;&amp; systemctl enable iptables\"</pre>\r\niptables setting\r\n\r\nsave iptables saat restart\r\nnano /etc/sysconfig/iptables-config\r\nfind : IPTABLES_SAVE_ON_RESTART=\"no\"\r\n\"change to yes\"\r\n\r\nadd iptables\r\nnote if theres firewalld then stop\r\n<pre>systemctl stop firewalld\r\nsystemctl mask firewalld</pre>\r\nadd iptables.\r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -s 192.168.7.0/24 -j SNAT --to-source [YOUR VPS IP ADDRESS]</pre>\r\n<pre>iptables-save</pre>\r\ncek iptables \r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -L</pre>\r\nif you need to delete iptables rules\r\n<pre>iptables --table nat --flush</pre>\r\n\r\n<pre>service dnsmasq restart\r\nservice vpnserver restart</pre>\r\n\"better reboot\"\r\n\r\ncek port/service running\r\n<pre>netstat -ntlp (cek via tcpv4)\r\nnetstat -ntlpu (cek via tcp6)</pre>','Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7','','inherit','closed','closed','','98-revision-v1','','','2018-01-11 15:57:08','2018-01-11 08:57:08','',98,'http://io99.softether.net/?p=100',0,'revision','',0),(101,1,'2018-01-11 15:58:03','2018-01-11 08:58:03','<strong>Local Bridge on Softether VPN Centos7</strong>\r\n\r\n!create local bridge on Softether VPN Manager Server window\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://imgur.com/fyGXqkO\"><img title=\"source: imgur.com\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/fyGXqkO.png\" /></a>\r\n\r\ngo terminal type: ifconfig\r\nthe name adapter we created : tap_\"[nama adapater]\".\r\ninstall dnsmasq\r\n<pre>yum -y install dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl start dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl stop dnsmasq\r\nsystemctl enabled dnsmasq\r\n\r\n\"now we can \"\r\nservice dnsmasq restart\r\n</pre>\r\nedit /etc/dnsmasq.conf\r\n\"add this\"\r\n<pre>interface=tap_soft\r\ndhcp-range=tap_soft,192.168.7.50,192.168.7.60,12h\r\ndhcp-option=tap_soft,3,192.168.7.1\r\nport=0\r\ndhcp-option=option:dns-server,[dns-server] ---&gt; biasa 8.8.8.8 atau 91.239.100.100</pre>\r\nnano /etc/init.d/vpnserver\r\n\"add line TAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1 and\r\nsleep 1\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR \"\r\n<pre>#!/bin/sh\r\n### BEGIN INIT INFO\r\n# Provides: vpnserver\r\n# Required-Start: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Required-Stop: $remote_fs $syslog\r\n# Default-Start: 2 3 4 5\r\n# Default-Stop: 0 1 6\r\n# Short-Description: Start daemon at boot time\r\n# Description: Enable Softether by daemon.\r\n### END INIT INFO\r\nDAEMON=/usr/local/vpnserver/vpnserver\r\nLOCK=/var/lock/subsys/vpnserver\r\nTAP_ADDR=192.168.7.1                          #&lt;-- add this\r\n\r\ntest -x $DAEMON || exit 0\r\ncase \"$1\" in\r\nstart)\r\n$DAEMON start\r\ntouch $LOCK\r\nsleep 1                                                      #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR           #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\nstop)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nrm $LOCK\r\n;;\r\nrestart)\r\n$DAEMON stop\r\nsleep 3\r\n$DAEMON start\r\nsleep 1                                                    #&lt;-- add this\r\n/sbin/ifconfig tap_soft $TAP_ADDR         #&lt;-- add this\r\n;;\r\n*)\r\necho \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|restart}\"\r\nexit 1\r\nesac\r\nexit 0</pre>\r\nedit /etc/sysctl.d/ipv4_forwarding.conf\r\nadd this :\r\n<pre>net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1</pre>\r\napply sysctl run\r\n<pre>sysctl --system</pre>\r\n\"if iptables package not installed :\r\n<pre>yum install iptables-services lalu systemctl start iptables &amp;&amp; systemctl enable iptables\"</pre>\r\niptables setting\r\n\r\nsave iptables saat restart\r\nnano /etc/sysconfig/iptables-config\r\nfind : IPTABLES_SAVE_ON_RESTART=\"no\"\r\n\"change to yes\"\r\nor to save iptables using yum install iptables-persistent\r\n\r\nadd iptables\r\nnote if theres firewalld then stop\r\n<pre>systemctl stop firewalld\r\nsystemctl mask firewalld</pre>\r\nadd iptables.\r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -s 192.168.7.0/24 -j SNAT --to-source [YOUR VPS IP ADDRESS]</pre>\r\n<pre>iptables-save</pre>\r\ncek iptables \r\n<pre>iptables -t nat -L</pre>\r\nif you need to delete iptables rules\r\n<pre>iptables --table nat --flush</pre>\r\n\r\n<pre>service dnsmasq restart\r\nservice vpnserver restart</pre>\r\n\"better reboot\"\r\n\r\ncek port/service running\r\n<pre>netstat -ntlp (cek via tcpv4)\r\nnetstat -ntlpu (cek via tcp6)</pre>','